ol.li:
Perform two separate searches in Qdrant:
One using the primary vector (goals_vector or hobbies_vector).
One using the general_vector. (Fetch more results than N, e.g., M=50)
Calculate a weighted score for each unique user: final = (w1 * primary_score) + (w2 * general_score)
Sort users by the final_score and return the Top N.

g.text: 3. Merge, Weight, Sort -> Final Top N
